Kubernetes is never used alone.
It sits at the center of a massive ecosystem.

Cluster Management: EKS, AKS, GKE, Rancher, kOps, OpenShift, Kubeadm
Infra Automation: Terraform, CloudFormation, Ansible, Pulumi, ARM
Container Runtimes: Docker, Containerd, CRI-O, rkt
Networking: Calico, Flannel, Weave, Cilium, kube-router
Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana, ELK, Datadog, Sysdig, New Relic, Dynatrace, AppDynamics, Zabbix

Master Kubernetes âžœ but also master the ecosystem that powers it.
